===Other accolades===
[[File:Gen Brown 160th SOAR compound ceremony.jpg|thumb|right|The dedication ceremony for renaming the 160th SOAR compound the "GEN Bryan "Doug" Brown Compound"]]

Shortly after his retirement, Brown was named "Patriot of the Year" for 2007 by the Congressional [[Medal of Honor]] Society, and he also received the [[Ellis Island Medal of Honor]].{{r|secureenergy}}{{r|harvard}} The following year, he was inducted into the Army Aviation Hall of Fame.{{r|AviationHoF}}{{r|secureenergy}} The Association of Special Operations Professionals named Brown "Man of the Year" in 2011.{{r|defensemedianetwork2}} In 2012, the 160th SOAR compound at Fort Campbell was renamed the "Gen. Bryan "Doug" Brown Compound" in his honor.{{r|EaglePost}}{{r|soc.mil}}

